plant_concentrations.Value: The head space constituents of living jasmine flowers contains 3% cis-jasmone(1). Flowers of Japanese honeysuckle (Lonicera japonica) were found to contain cis-jasmone concentrations of 80-602 ug/kg(2). Jasmone was identified in the volatile components of kiwi fruit flowers (Actinidia chinensis Planch)(3). cis-Jasmone is found in the essential oils of jasmine (3%), jonquil, and Pittosporam glabratum, in neroli oil, in peppermint (Mentha piperita), and in bergamont, apricot, raspberry, cinnamon, corn mint and spearmint oils, tea, and soybean(4). cis-Jasmone was detected in the essential oil composition of Feronia elephantum Correa (family: Rutaceae)(5).
